Title: Library Rules and Regulations for  Emerson University Multan Pakistan
1. General Conduct..Maintain silence in all areas of the library..Mobile phones must be kept on silent mode. Avoid calls inside the reading halls. Eating
Author: drinking
Genre: and smoking are strictly prohibited.Treat library property with care. Any damage or theft will result in disciplinary action.

Title: 2. Library Membership..Only registered students
Author: faculty
Genre: and staff are allowed to use the library.Library cards are non-transferable.Report any lost or stolen cards immediately.

Title: 3. Borrowing Books..Books can be borrowed by showing a valid university ID.Students may borrow up to 3 books for 14 days.Books must be returned or renewed before the due date to avoid fines.
4. Fines and Penalties..A fine of Rs. 10 per day will be charged for each overdue book.Lost or damaged books must be replaced or paid for in full.
5. Reading Room Rules..Personal belongings (bags
Author: files) must be placed in the designated area..Only notebooks and reading materials are allowed inside.Seats cannot be reserved; unattended items may be removed.

Title: 6. Digital Library & Internet Use..Computers are for academic purposes only.Do not install
Author: download
Genre: or alter any software.Accessing inappropriate or non-academic sites is strictly prohibited.

Title: 7. Respect for Others...Be courteous to library staff and fellow users.
Follow all instructions given by the library personnel.
